But we are to remember that Bocchus is talking to persons whom he sup- poses to be, and who probably at this time really were ignorant of the articles stipulated betwixt him and J ugurtha3 and, therefore, we are the less to wonder that he makes insinuations of what was not precisely true, especially considering that this would have the appearance of a pretty plausible apology for his past eonduct.—M.
